Takealot has opened pre-orders for the Apple iPhone 11, 11 Pro, and 11 Pro Max. The new iPhone is available in a range of colours and storage sizes from Takealot, starting with the iPhone 11 64GB and going up to the iPhone 11 Pro Max 512GB. Pre-orders of the device will start shipping on 27 September 2019. Takealot is also running a special for the first 50 shoppers who complete their iPhone 11 pre-order. The first 50 shoppers with confirmed payment for their iPhone 11 pre-order will receive a R1,000 Takealot voucher, for use on their next order. Terms and conditions do apply. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-320681 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/iPhone-order-640x259.jpg" alt="iPhone order" width="640" height="259" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/iPhone-order-640x259.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/iPhone-order-600x243.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/iPhone-order.jpg 740w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> This article was published in partnership with Takealot.